New Georgia Group. Kolombangara. Mt. Duke. Along main ridge to summit of Mt. Duke, which is a small peak, 1350 m high, south of Mt. Tapalamenggutu and north of the Vila River. Mossy montane forest with spongy, humis soil. Plants preserved in alcohol. Guide Phillip Rini. Good trail to summit begins at end of logging road at 350 m, with 4-5 hour hike to peak.
